rComments: Just an incredible prof. 10/10 recommend, clear grading criteria, assigned an average amount of work. The class was super interesting as well.

I absolutely loved Prof. Kmiec's class, one of my favorites at the university so far! It was a condensed summer class, but she did a great job at balancing the number of readings we had with video clips, and everything she assigned was super interesting. A fantastic class to take, with a lecturer that makes you see the world a different way!

I really liked her as a prof. We had quite a few marked things, including discussion board posts (which you had all year to do) and a couple short in-class assignments (told you in advance), which took the pressure off if you got a bad mark on one thing. She also adapted so well to switching to online during the pandemic. I highly recommend

Professor Kmiec is one of my all-time favourite professors. She teaches in Gender Studies as well as History, though I have only had the opportunity to take a few of her history courses. She is a great professor to listen to, and is really, really passionate about what she teaches and helping her students succeed.

She's great as a prof, but my oh my are her tests impossible. I was lucky enough to have her in His2100, where there were no tests, but the few quizzes I had had me scratching my head and stressed as ever. Avoid her if you want an A.
Nice, caring, and friendly for sure. Mediocre prof and lecturer. Assignment instructions are clear, but lecture slides are not particularly informative. Rarely refers to the textbook.

Such a great prof! Really cares about the material which makes is so much more interesting! She didn't give a midterm or final and had LOTS of small assignments that were just mark boosters. Continuously gave bonus assignments too if people in the class weren't doing great not sure how that could even happen though because she grades really easily

I liked her a lot. She's very knowledgeable about the material and taught in a very effective way. I wouldn't say shes easy but definitely a good class. if you have to take research, trust me she will make you understand it. I would definitely take her class again, she makes me love my program more.

Prof reads off sheet entire lecture & loses her spot frequently. Readings are very academic. You must take lecture notes as her PP slides are minimal. Assignments during semester aren't too hard. Final exam was crazy. 6 questions, 20+ pages of academic writing in 2 hours. She must have bell-curved. Prof is decent, friendly-ish, smart, dry humour.

She was stellar! I enjoyed her class very much and it was always interesting. Marks very fairly, and in-class assignments got me to really engage in the subject. Really described exactly what you needed to do well and how to achieve in the course. Take her if you can!

Yes, there is a A LOT of readings -- but take key examples from each (including title + author) and take diligent notes in class. Overall, she is fair if you can show you know the material using examples. Also, just writing something on the class assignments gets you marks!
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Easily one of my favourite professors. She made sure that her instructions were always clear, whether it was how to get a bonus mark or how to prep for the midterm + final. You will have to do the readings + take notes in class, but this is university and that's very common. She made sure to interact and get our opinions, and was very approachable.

Get ready to read textbooks that are difficult to understand and painful to read. There is no Study guide for both mid-term and exam. Most questions on the tests are from the text books on facts that have no relation to the course, and was not mentioned in class. I would not take her course again.

I just want to start off by saying that I had such optimistic expectations for this course. Unfortunately, Professor Kmiec decided that because there were a lot of 4th years in the second year class, she would teach it as a 4th year course. Unnecessary amount of readings too, she's the reason I dropped my Women's Studies minor.

She doesn't provide study guides for either the final or midterm exam, she only reads off the slides and doesn't explain things properly and her slides have little information on them and both textbooks are awful and hard to understand
Pretty good class. She is funny and the assignment was easy. You have to do the readings to pass the tests.

She reads her lecture off of a paper the whole time and can't complete a full sentence without taking a 5-10 second pause between words. Could have easily gotten all the information from the slides without going to the lecture. Also lots of reading and the test mainly based off of the readings, not the lecture material.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Very slow, expected readings to be memorized.

The teacher does give a lot of assignments, but they are easy and are simply there to ensure that you are doing the readings for the course. She does not have a text book (you save money), but you do have a lot of electric readings. She truly cares about the course. she created 5 different sections on the exams while as a student you get to do 2.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Amazing lectures ', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: An insightful, well-spoken, and concise prof with a great, dry sense of humour*. I had more "ah-ha!" moments in their (logically structured) lectures than in most of my courses throughout uni and thought marking was fair (albeit strict). *Note: students who spoke before really thinking did get short responses/ probably didn't like this as much

I'm in my 4th year of sociology at uOttawa and she is one of the best profs I've had. There are small in-class assignments throughout the term that are not hard if you've done the readings, midterm and exam expectations are clear, and she's genuinely a great lecturer. I would highly recommend, looking forward to taking another class with her.

Really good prof! Class wasn't too hard but not too easy either. Make sure to go to class tough; there are unannounced (for the most part) in class assignments. They're really easy and a good grade booster.
Great prof! Great class. The exam is hard, but there is a lot of light work to make up for it. If u go to class, you'll be fine.

Prof was condescending responding with "ya" and "mhm" after students answered her qs. Wrote 4 papers. Final exam needed to bring in as many sources from course readings and do an in depth critical analysis with attention paid to spelling and grammar, without going over 2 pages double spaced:S. My cgpa is 9.2 but she liked to call 'our group' weak
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'So many papers']
